summary: An ordinance relating to and providing for the improvement of Temple Place in the City of Seattle, from East Cherry Street to the south line of Tract "J" of the S. B. Yesler Tracts, by grading the same and constructing concrete sidewalks thereon, together with wooden curbs and gutters and cross walks, in accordance with Majority Petition No. 31394 and providing payment therefor by the mode of "Payment in Bonds", as provided by the laws of the State of Washington and the Charter and Ordinances of the City of Seattle.
